      • next

        public int[] next​(int count)
        Returns the next count int's in increasing order. If count is greater than 26, then duplicates will be returned.
        Parameters:
        count - any int value is permitted (less than 1 returns a zero-len array)

      • nextRandom

        public int[] nextRandom​(int count)
        Returns count int's randomly chosen from the available 26 int's and the returned result may include duplicates. If reset() is called, then the same sequence of 'random' int's is returned.
        Parameters:
        count - any int value is permitted (less than 1 returns a zero-len array)

      • getInts

        public static int[] getInts​(int count)
        Returns the number of int's requested in sequence. There are 26 int's, so they wrap around and repeat as needed.
        Parameters:
        count - any int value is permitted (less than 1 returns a zero-len array)

      • getInts

        public static int[] getInts​(int offset,
                            int count)
        Returns the number of int's requested in sequence starting at the specified offset. There are 26 int's, so they wrap around and repeat as needed.
        Parameters:
        offset - any int value is permitted (less than zero is silently increased to zero)
        count - any int value is permitted (less than 1 returns a zero-len array)
